  "description": "<p>\n\t<img src=\"http://n1image.hjfile.cn/mh/2016/12/09/59a18695c44168e9bbbb5279ed9b2f60.jpg\" /></p>\n<p>\n\t<strong>由不及物动词+介词或副词形成的被动语态</strong></p>\n<p>\n\tMany trees are cut down by workers.</p>\n<p>\n\t许多树木被工人砍倒。</p>\n<p>\n\t不及物动词不能跟宾语，当然就没有被动语态了，但有的不及物动词，后面跟上一个介词或副词后（即形成所谓的动词短语），其作用和一个及物动词一样，这样，在变成被动语态时，千万不要把介词或副词去掉。</p>\n<p>\n\t例如：</p>\n<p>\n\tShe looks after them.</p>\n<p>\n\t她照顾他们。</p>\n<p>\n\t（○）They are looked after by her.</p>\n<p>\n\t（&times;）They are looked by her.</p>\n<p>\n\tWe laughed at him.</p>\n<p>\n\t我们笑话他。</p>\n<p>\n\tHe was laughed at（by us）.</p>\n<p>\n\t&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n\t<strong>动词短语的被动语态</strong></p>\n<p>\n\ttake care of（照看）&rarr;be taken care of</p>\n<p>\n\tcut down（砍倒）&rarr;be cut down</p>\n<p>\n\tlaugh at（嘲笑）&rarr;be laughed at</p>\n<p>\n\tlook after（照料）&rarr;be looked after</p>\n<p>\n\t&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n\t<strong>被动语态的动词短语</strong></p>\n<p>\n\t以下这些短语本身即是被动语态的形式，不需再加&ldquo;by&rdquo;。</p>\n<p>\n\tbe covered with&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;用&hellip;&hellip;覆盖着</p>\n<p>\n\tbe surprised at&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;对&hellip;&hellip;感到惊奇</p>\n<p>\n\tbe known to&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;出名</p>\n<p>\n\tbe interested in&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;对&hellip;&hellip;感兴趣</p>\n<p>\n\tbe made of（from）&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;用&hellip;&hellip;制造的</p>\n<br /><center><a href=\"http://www.hjenglish.com/new/p959921/#relate_articles\"><img src=\"http://en.hujiang.com/2009/images/rss_chat.jpg\" style=\"border: 0;\" /></a> <a href=\"http://www.hjenglish.com/new/p959921\"><img src=\"http://en.hujiang.com/2009/images/rss_digg.jpg\" style=\"border: 0;\